SIMPLE: urn
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Urn
<hw>Urn</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>urne</ets>, L.
<ets>urna</ets>; perhaps fr. <ets>urere</ets> to burn, and sop called as
being made of burnt clay (cf. <er>East</er>): cf. F.
<ets>urne</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A vessel of various forms, usually a vase furnished
with a foot or pedestal, employed for different purposes, as for holding
liquids, for ornamental uses, for preserving the ashes of the dead after
cremation, and anciently for holding lots to be drawn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A rustic, digging in the ground by Padua, found an <qex>urn</qex>,
or earthen pot, in which there was another <qex>urn</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Wilkins.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His scattered limbs with my dead body burn,⟦br⟧
And once more join us in the pious <qex>urn</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: Any place of burial; the grave.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Or lay these bones in an unworthy <qex>urn</qex>,⟦br⟧
Tombless, with no remembrance over them.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A measure of capacity for
liquids, containing about three gallons and a haft, wine measure. It was
haft the amphora, and four times the congius.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A hollow body shaped like an urn,
in which the spores of mosses are contained; a spore case; a
theca.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A tea urn. See under <er>Tea</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Urn mosses</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>the order of
true mosses; -- so called because the capsules of many kinds are
urn-shaped.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Urn</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Urn
<hw>Urn</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To inclose in, or as in, an urn; to
inurn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> When horror universal shall descend,⟦br⟧
And heaven's dark concave <qex>urn</qex> all human race.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Urnal</ent>⟦br⟧
